result.CacheCacheStatus: string; cache status. Possible values are unknown | miss | expired | updating | stale | hit | ignored | bypass | revalidated | dynamic | stream_hit | deferred "dynamic" means that a request is not eligible for cache. This can mean, for example that it was blocked by the firewall. Refer to [Cloudflare cache responses](https://developers.cloudflare.com/cache/about/default-cache-behavior/#cloudflare-cache-responses) for more details.
result.CacheResponseBytes: int; number of bytes returned by the cache
result.CacheResponseStatus: int; HTTP status code returned by the cache to the edge. All requests (including non-cacheable ones) go through the cache. Refer also to CacheCacheStatus field.
result.CacheTieredFill: bool; tiered Cache was used to serve this request
result.ClientCountry: string; country of the client IP address
result.ClientIP: string; IP address of the client
result.ClientIPClass: string; unknown | badHost | searchEngine | allowlist | monitoringService | noRecord | scan | tor
result.ClientMTLSAuthCertFingerprint: string; the SHA256 fingerprint of the certificate presented by the client during mTLS authentication. Only populated on the first request on an mTLS connection. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.ClientMTLSAuthStatus: string; the status of mTLS authentication. Only populated on the first request on an mTLS connection. Available in Logpush v2 only. Possible values are unknown | ok | absent | untrusted | notyetvalid | expired
result.ClientRequestBytes: int; number of bytes in the client request
result.ClientRequestHost: string; host requested by the client
result.ClientRequestMethod: string; HTTP method of client request
result.ClientRequestPath: string; URI path requested by the client
result.ClientRequestProtocol: string; HTTP protocol of client request
result.ClientRequestScheme: string; the URL scheme requested by the visitor. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.ClientRequestSource: string; identifies requests as coming from an external source or another service within Cloudflare. Refer to [ClientRequestSource field](https://developers.cloudflare.com/logs/reference/clientrequestsource/) for the list of potential values. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.ClientRequestURI: string; URI requested by the client
result.ClientRequestUserAgent: string; user agent reported by the client
result.ClientSSLProtocol: string; client SSL (TLS) protocol. The value "none" means that SSL was not used.
result.ClientTCPRTTMs: int; the smoothed average of TCP round-trip time (SRTT). For the initial request on a connection, this is measured only during connection setup. For a subsequent request on the same connection, it is measured over the entire connection lifetime up until the time that request is received. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.Cookies: object; string key-value pairs for Cookies
result.EdgeCFConnectingO2O: bool; true if the request looped through multiple zones on the Cloudflare edge. This is considered an orange to orange (o2o) request. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.EdgeColoCode: string; IATA airport code of data center that received the request
result.EdgeEndTimestamp: int or string; timestamp at which the edge finished sending response to the client
result.EdgePathingOp: string; indicates what type of response was issued for this request (unknown = no specific action)
result.EdgePathingSrc: string; details how the request was classified based on security checks (unknown = no specific classification)
result.EdgePathingStatus: string; indicates what data was used to determine the handling of this request (unknown = no data)
result.EdgeRateLimitAction: string; the action taken by the blocking rule; empty if no action taken. Possible values are unknown | simulate | ban | challenge | jsChallenge
result.EdgeRateLimitID: int; the internal rule ID of the rate-limiting rule that triggered a block (ban) or log action. 0 if no action taken.
result.EdgeRequestHost: string; host header on the request from the edge to the origin
result.EdgeResponseBodyBytes: int; size of the HTTP response body returned to clients. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.EdgeResponseBytes: int; number of bytes returned by the edge to the client
result.EdgeResponseContentType: string; edge response Content-Type header value
result.EdgeResponseStatus: int; HTTP status code returned by Cloudflare to the client
result.EdgeServerIP: string; IP of the edge server making a request to the origin. Possible responses are string in IPv4 or IPv6 format, or empty string. Empty string means that there was no request made to the origin server.
result.EdgeStartTimestamp: int or string; timestamp at which the edge received request from the client
result.EdgeTimeToFirstByteMs: int; total view of Time To First Byte as measured at Cloudflare's edge. Starts after a TCP connection is established and ends when Cloudflare begins returning the first byte of a response to eyeballs. Includes TLS handshake time (for new connections) and origin response time. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.FirewallMatchesActions: array[string]; array of actions the Cloudflare firewall products performed on this request. The individual firewall products associated with this action be found in FirewallMatchesSources and their respective RuleIds can be found in FirewallMatchesRuleIDs. The length of the array is the same as FirewallMatchesRuleIDs and FirewallMatchesSources. Possible actions are unknown | allow | block | challenge | jschallenge | log | connectionClose | challengeSolved | challengeFailed | challengeBypassed | jschallengeSolved | jschallengeFailed | jschallengeBypassed | bypass | managedChallenge | managedChallengeSkipped | managedChallengeNonInteractiveSolved | managedChallengeInteractiveSolved | managedChallengeBypassed
result.FirewallMatchesRuleIDs: array[string]; array of RuleIDs of the firewall product that has matched the request. The firewall product associated with the RuleID can be found in FirewallMatchesSources. The length of the array is the same as FirewallMatchesActions and FirewallMatchesSources.
result.FirewallMatchesSources: array[string]; the firewall products that matched the request. The same product can appear multiple times, which indicates different rules or actions that were activated. The RuleIDs can be found in FirewallMatchesRuleIDs, the actions can be found in FirewallMatchesActions. The length of the array is the same as FirewallMatchesRuleIDs and FirewallMatchesActions. Validation matches only appear in Logpush and are not supported in Logpull. Possible sources are unknown | asn | country | ip | ipRange | securityLevel | zoneLockdown | waf | firewallRules | uaBlock | rateLimit | bic | hot | l7ddos | validation | botFight | apiShield | botManagement | dlp | firewallManaged | firewallCustom
result.OriginDNSResponseTimeMs: int; time taken to receive a DNS response for an origin name. Usually 0, but may be longer if a CNAME record is used. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.OriginIP: string; IP of the origin server
result.OriginRequestHeaderSendDurationMs: int; timeÂ taken to send request headers to origin after establishing a connection. Note that this value is usually 0. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.OriginResponseBytes: int; number of bytes returned by the origin server
result.OriginResponseDurationMs: int; upstream response time, measured from the first datacenter that receives a request. Includes time taken by Argo Smart Routing and Tiered Cache, plus time to connect and receive a response from origin servers. This field replaces OriginResponseTime. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.OriginResponseHTTPExpires: string; value of the origin 'expires' header in RFC1123 format
result.OriginResponseHTTPLastModified: string; value of the origin 'last-modified' header in RFC1123 format
result.OriginResponseHeaderReceiveDurationMs: int; time taken for origin to return response headers after Cloudflare finishes sending request headers. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.OriginResponseStatus: int; status returned by the origin server. The value 0 means that there was no request made to the origin server and the response was served by Cloudflare's Edge.
result.OriginResponseTime: int; number of nanoseconds it took the origin to return the response to edge
result.OriginSSLProtocol: string; SSL (TLS) protocol used to connect to the origin
result.OriginTCPHandshakeDurationMs: int; time taken to complete TCP handshake with origin. This will be 0 if an origin connection is reused. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.OriginTLSHandshakeDurationMs: int; time taken to complete TLS handshake with origin. This will be 0 if an origin connection is reused. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.ParentRayID: string; Ray ID of the parent request if this request was made using a Worker script
result.RequestHeaders: object; string key-value pairs for RequestHeaders
result.ResponseHeaders: object; string key-value pairs for ResponseHeaders
result.SecurityLevel: string; the security level configured at the time of this request. This is used to determine the sensitivity of the IP Reputation system.
result.SmartRouteColoID: int; the Cloudflare datacenter used to connect to the origin server if Argo Smart Routing is used. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.UpperTierColoID: int; the "upper tier" datacenter that was checked for a cached copy if Tiered Cache is used. Available in Logpush v2 only.
result.WAFAction: string; action taken by the WAF, if triggered
result.WAFFlags: string; additional configuration flags: simulate (0x1) | null
result.WAFMatchedVar: string; the full name of the most-recently matched variable
result.WAFRuleID: string; ID of the applied WAF rule
result.WAFRuleMessage: string; rule message associated with the triggered rule
result.WorkerCPUTime: int; amount of time in microseconds spent executing a worker, if any
result.WorkerStatus: string; status returned from worker daemon
result.WorkerSubrequest: bool; whether or not this request was a worker subrequest
result.WorkerSubrequestCount: int; number of subrequests issued by a worker when handling this request
result.ZoneName: string; the human-readable name of the zone (e.g. 'cloudflare.com'). Available in Logpush v2 only.
